# Frontend Rules

## Stack

- **Next.js 16** (App Router), **React 19**, **TypeScript**
- **Tailwind CSS** for styling; use **class-variance-authority (CVA)** with **clsx** and **tailwind-merge** for conditional/variant styles
- **TanStack React Query** for server state; **Zod** for validation
- **Radix UI** / **shadcn** components in `src/components/ui/`

## Conventions

- Use **functional components** and **hooks** only; no class components.
- Prefer **server components** where possible; use `"use client"` only when needed (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs).
- Colocate components under `src/components/` by feature (e.g. `dashboard/`, `library/`, `ui/`).
- Use **typed props** with interfaces; avoid `any`.
- For forms and API payloads, **validate with Zod** and surface errors in the UI.
- Use **React Query** for fetching/mutations; keep loading and error states explicit in the UI.
- Use **semantic HTML** and **accessible patterns** (labels, ARIA where needed); prefer Radix/shadcn primitives for complex widgets.
- Keep **client-side state** minimal; lift state only as needed and prefer URL/search params for shareable state where appropriate.
- Use **shadcn ui** as much as possible when implementing the frontend.

## Design tokens (Tailwind)

- **Do not** use Tailwind **`gray-*` / `slate-*`** scales in `className` strings — map to semantic tokens: `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `bg-background`, `bg-card`, `bg-popover`, and `text-foreground/[0.xx]` when you need stepped contrast. ESLint warns on `className="…gray-…"` / `slate-` (template literals are not covered).
- **Tables and dense lists** should use shared helpers from `src/lib/list-ui.ts` where possible.

## Modals and floating surfaces

- **Centered dialogs** (`DialogContent`): default shell is **`bg-background`** with `border-border` (see `src/components/ui/dialog.tsx`). Override with `bg-background` unless you need a deliberate lift (`bg-card` for nested emphasis only).
- **Dropdown-style panels** (menus, autocomplete lists): prefer **`bg-popover`** and **`text-popover-foreground`** so they match `dropdown-menu` / `popover`.
- **AlertDialog**: when added, use the same **`bg-background`** rule as `DialogContent`.

## Focus visible

- **Global** `globals.css` sets a single **`:focus-visible` outline** for native focusables. **shadcn `Button`** and several Radix triggers use **`focus-visible:ring-*`** instead; avoid adding a second global rule that duplicates the same outline on `button`/`a`/`input` (that stacks visually). Prefer **ring on components** for custom controls; keep **outline** for unstyled native elements.
